WHILE PRACTICING HOVERING THE HELICOPTER BEGAN TO DRIFT. THE 
INSTRUCTOR PILOT CORRECTED THIS AND RETURNED CONTROL TO THE STUDENT PILOT. 
THE HELICOPTER THEN BEGAN TO DESCEND AND THE INSTRUCTOR PILOT ATTEMPTED 
TO CORRECT THIS WITH COLLECTIVE, BUT THE STUDENT PILOT APPLIED OPPOSITE 
COLLECTIVE INPUT. A SKID CAUGHT THE GROUND AND THE HELICOPTER THEN 
EXPERIENCED DYNAMIC ROLLOVER. THE STUDENT HAD 7 HOURS OF TOTAL FLIGHT 
TIME. 
